SSH Server: Password Authentication configure SSH server to manage a server from remote computer, SSH client.

Step 01 :- Check apt is up to date
Command : sudo apt-get update

Step 02 :- Install openssh-server
Command : sudo apt-get install openssh-server

Step 03 :- Start ssh server
Command : sudo systemctl start ssh

Step 04 :-  Enable SSH
Command : sudo systemctl enable ssh

step 05 :- check the status of ssh  
Command :- sudo systemctl status ssh

Step 06 :- Install firewall (ufw)
Command : sudo ufw allow ssh

Step 07 :- Enable firewall 
Command : sudo ufw enable

Step 08 :- Check the status of firewall
Command : sudo ufw status

Step 09 :- Test your connection
Command : ssh username@ip   (eg. ssh kali@127.0.01)
